commit.message:
Use Ubuntu bionic for TravisCI

Also:
- Deploy under Python 3.7
- Update psycopg2 requirement to a version compatible with glibc 2.26 for
  Galaxy releases 16.01-18.01
- Drop support for old Galaxy releases 15.03 - 17.05 which don't start
  without multiple patches due to broken Python eggs/wheels download: see
  e.g. https://travis-ci.org/github/galaxyproject/bioblend/builds/665803989
  for eggs, while for wheels the psycopg2 fix above doesn't work without
  passing the `--extra-index-url` option to `pip`
Install virtualenv >=20.0.14 to fix conda commands on macOS

Remove unused code

Galaxy releases without `scripts/common_startup.sh` are not supported
any more.
